# RDS Tracker — Project Overview

Companion web app for [Dr. Dave's Runout Drill System](https://drdavepoolinfo.com/faq/drill/rds/) (BU Exam IV progressive/adaptive format). Credit Dr. Dave via the level-select byline; do not republish his instructional content beyond brief rule summaries already in the catalog.

## What it does

- Shows current RDS level: diagram, rules, skill rating
- 3-rack win/loss grid with submit gating and official level-up/down rules (2+ wins → +1, 1 win → stay, 0 wins → −1; clamp 1–16)
- Persists frame + rack history locally; shows per-level W/L stats on level page and level picker
- **RDS 100** scored format is out of scope

## Module layout

| Path | Responsibility |
|------|----------------|
| `src/modules/level-catalog/` | Static levels 1–16, `GENERAL_RULES`, rack diagram specs |
| `src/modules/frame-scoring/` | Pure `scoreFrame()` logic — no I/O |
| `src/modules/session/` | In-progress `FrameDraft` helpers (`toggleRackCell`, `canSubmitFrame`, etc.) |
| `src/modules/persistence/` | `RdsStore` + `PersistenceAdapter`; currently `localStorage` |
| `src/modules/stats/` | `computeLevelStats`, win-rate formatting/color |
| `src/components/` | React UI only; no business rules |
| `src/types.ts` | Shared types (`AppData`, `FrameRecord`, `RackRecord`, …) |

Keep logic in modules; components orchestrate and render. Extend via `PersistenceAdapter`, not by bypassing `RdsStore`.

## UI conventions

- Mobile-first: play screen should fit one phone viewport (compact diagram box, no general rules on level page)
- General RDS rules collapsible lives on **level select only**
- Stats: green wins, red losses, gradient averages (0 → red, .333 → yellow, .666+ → green)
- Frame win = 2+ racks in frame; rack stats = individual win/loss at that level

## Deployment

- Live site: `gh-pages` branch (built `dist/`), **https://operationivy.github.io/RDSTracker/**
- `vite.config.ts` uses `base: "/RDSTracker/"`
- Publish: `npm run deploy` (build + gh-pages push). GitHub Pages is static only — no server-side storage.

